      "<hr/>",
      "# Fusion Reactor",
      "<br/>",
      "  Did you have fun with /b/Nuclear Fission/b/? Well, it's time for /b/Nuclear Fusion/b/! Instead of splitting a heavy, unstable nucleus into two lighter nuclei, /b/fusion/b/ will combine together two light nuclei which in turn releases vast amounts of energy. This energy can be contained and used to produce /b/Helium Plasma/b/, an extremely energy dense fluid that can be used as the best power source in the world.",
      "<br/>",
      "  You can combine gaseous fuels such as /b/Deuterium/b/, /b/Tritium/b/ and/or /b/Helium-3/b/ to produce various combinations of Helium Plasma, Tritium, Deuterium, and Hydrogen. Keep in mind, this fusion takes a lot of energy to start going, but can produce much more as a result.",
